Martin Mares wrote:
>> 	Hello All,  This would be a very good approach .
>> 	A BGP respondable mail exploder ... ;-)
>   Unfortunately, BGP doesn't give enough information since you need
>to know routing information as seen from _all_ your exploders.
Oh, it would work pretty well.  Just sort exploders by AS numbers (get a
BGP table form all the exploders once a month, build a list of "best
connected ASes" for each of them), then just one lookup for the AS number
of the best MX would be sufficient.
